1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,999
Mr. Chan has brought Ms. Claire here.

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,440
If I say your aunt is still alive,
will you listen to me?

3
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,719
As long as you agree to be Claire,

4
00:00:18,720 --> 00:00:21,759
<i>your aunt will receive
the best possible care.</i>

5
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:24,199
Chan was the one who said Claire was dead.

6
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:26,199
<i>So how could he bring her home?</i>

7
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:29,959
<i>Dad, don't you remember
what Claire did to me before the crash?</i>

8
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:31,279
Just once.

9
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,279
<i>I wouldn't have stopped you</i>

10
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:36,439
if she could remember what she did to you.

11
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:38,440
<i>Claire is suffering from amnesia.</i>

12
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,600
What's wrong now?

13
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:56,960
You want me to fake amnesia?

14
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:00,240
It's the only way to avoid suspicion.

15
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:03,599
Besides, you don't know
everything about Claire.

16
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,879
There's no way you can imitate her 100%.

17
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:07,119
I see.

18
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:10,840
So you cooked up this lie
that I have amnesia?

19
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:13,479
Why didn't you tell them from the start?

20
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:16,479
I wouldn't have been so tense
I could barely breathe.

21
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:20,319
If I did that, you wouldn't take
being Claire seriously.

22
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:24,639
Besides, the amnesia excuse
won't work forever.

23
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:28,760
No matter what, you have to be
as much like Claire as possible

24
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:34,600
because you must become
TGL Group's chairwoman.

25
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:36,640
Say what?

26
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:41,800
You know how much
her grandfather loves her.

27
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:45,239
And he intends for her
to inherit everything.

28
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:46,640
Hold on, hold on.

29
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,319
That's not what we agreed on.

30
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:53,960
You made me Ms. Claire so her grandfather
wouldn't have a heart attack. That's it.

31
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:59,359
I remember exactly what we talked about,

32
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:04,920
but you becoming the chairwoman of
TGL Group is another wish of the chairman.

33
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:09,720
What if I refuse?

34
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,960
You don't really have a choice.

35
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,999
Hey.

36
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,280
Are you not listening to me at all, huh?

37
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,959
Take a shower and go to bed.

38
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:34,000
This is Claire's nightgown.
You have to wear this.

39
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:42,159
No way.
I'm not wearing something like that.

40
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,680
Do you know why I'm making you wear this?

41
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:47,719
Because you need to be Claire
as much as possible.

42
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,599
And no need to feel self-conscious.

43
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:52,840
No one will come in here
unless you call for them.

44
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:55,120
What about you?

45
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:57,720
Me?

46
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,280
I live in another house.

47
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:05,520
You...

48
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,560
You're not sleeping here?

49
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:14,079
You and Ms. Claire are engaged,
so I thought you two would...

50
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,400
Would sleep together?

51
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,800
Hey.

52
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:22,080
Can you tell the difference between
being engaged and being married?

53
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,320
Claire and I were just engaged.

54
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,799
I know.

55
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,079
I get that, but...

56
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:32,199
Ms. Claire...

57
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:35,120
seemed wild, so I thought you two...

58
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:40,799
Okay.

59
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,599
Okay, never mind. Forget it.

60
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,720
You can leave now,
so I can shower and go to bed.

61
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:48,960
Go on.

62
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:03,120
No way. I'm never wearing
something like this.

63
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,680
And it's so weird.

64
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,119
His fiancée literally died.

65
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,680
He doesn't seem sad at all.

66
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:44,439
Next time you're gonna freak out,
be done with it before you show up.

67
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:46,480
You can't do that in front of your dad.

68
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,119
What was I supposed to do?

69
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:52,039
Hide away like a bastard,
just because you're his mistress?

70
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,520
Do you have any idea
how much I want to kill her?

71
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:57,440
You don't think I want that too?

72
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:00,879
If she hadn't manipulated your dad,

73
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:03,080
would we be in this position?

74
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,719
4 YEARS AGO

75
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:11,319
And now, the moment
you've all been waiting for.

76
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:14,279
The award for The Best Woman of the Year.

77
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:19,879
And this year, it could be no one else
but Ms. Rossarin Charatphong!

78
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,120
Let's hear a round of applause.

79
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,400
Congratulations.

80
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:28,280
Please give her another round of applause.

81
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:33,400
Thank you for this award.

82
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,639
I am absolutely thrilled
and deeply honored.

83
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:41,439
As you all know, the Best Woman award

84
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:47,120
is something given only to
someone everyone truly respects.

85
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,160
Claire?

86
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:06,120
What are you doing?

87
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:08,199
Hello, everyone.

88
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,960
I'm Khaedarun,

89
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:13,559
the biological granddaughter of Mr. Thiwa,
TGL Group's chairman.

90
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,439
I had been told that Ms. Rossarin,

91
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,119
my grandpa's young wife,

92
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,119
and former housekeeper, won an award.

93
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:23,760
So I had to rush back from
America to congratulate her.

94
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:39,239
Nothing suits you, Aunt Rin,

95
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:42,480
better than this bouquet
of golden flowers.

96
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,520
Please take some photos.

97
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,800
Look this way, please. Beautiful.

98
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,400
Grandpa.

99
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:04,959
What's wrong?

100
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,920
Aren't you happy I'm back?

101
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,200
Why did you treat her like that?

102
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,120
Do you really want to know?

103
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:14,120
Claire.

104
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,279
You just got back from overseas.
You must be tired.

105
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:19,559
Why don't you go home and rest?
We'll talk later.

106
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,720
What the hell is wrong with you?

107
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:25,480
Who do you think you are,
some drama heroine?

108
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:26,960
Oh, really?

109
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:31,800
I thought your mom didn't fight back
because she had to play the heroine.

110
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,839
Wait. Did you not fight back

111
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:37,480
because you liked the flowers I gave you?

112
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,039
Save your sharp words.

113
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,640
They don't affect me at all.

114
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,519
I knew you wouldn't feel a thing,
Aunt Rin.

115
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:53,600
Otherwise, people wouldn't be gossiping
about your scandal all over town.

116
00:08:56,080 --> 00:09:01,679
Grandpa, do you want to know
why she deserves those golden flowers?

117
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,240
Are you not done being crazy?

118
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:06,920
The one who deserves
those golden flowers is you.

119
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,000
Anything else you want to say?

120
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,440
You don't actually believe
your granddaughter, do you?

121
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:19,439
You know she hates me.

122
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:23,200
Whenever she sees me getting ahead,
she finds ways to accuse me.

123
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,199
Aunt Rin.

124
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,399
Come on now.

125
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,359
You gotta own up to your actions.

126
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,719
Just tell him.

127
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:32,200
Either way, you two aren't
getting anything from him.

128
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,920
Shut your mouth.

129
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:44,640
It's you who needs to shut it.

130
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,720
- Chan, take me home.
- Right this way.

131
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,600
Mr. Thiwa!

132
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:57,240
It hurts, but it's worth it.

133
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:05,720
Ever since that day,
your dad's been cold to me.

134
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:09,400
She made him think I cheated on him.

135
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,480
Don't you worry.

136
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,160
I want Claire dead too.

137
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,320
In that case,

138
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:27,360
I'll kill her myself.

139
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,760
What are you gonna do?

140
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,479
Don't worry, Mom.

141
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:34,880
I didn't mean it literally.

142
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:37,920
But I'll make her life a living hell.

143
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:44,560
Especially now that she has amnesia,
I need to act fast.

144
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,760
<i>Let's get married.</i>

145
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,400
<i>I have just one question.</i>

146
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:06,520
<i>- Do you love me, Chan?
- Of course I do.</i>

147
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:12,479
<i>I told you to stay out of my business.</i>

148
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:15,440
<i>But your business is my business.</i>

149
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,760
And I am your fiancé.

150
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:22,959
<i>How many more men
do you need to be satisfied?</i>

151
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,320
<i>Do you want to kill me?</i>

152
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:49,279
<i>Oh, help me, please.</i>

153
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,600
<i>Help me.</i>

154
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:55,080
<i>Oh, help me, please.</i>

155
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,120
<i>You want to be me?</i>

156
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,400
Hey.

157
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:40,840
A nightmare?

158
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:47,800
If you woke up with someone else's face,
wouldn't you be terrified?

159
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,400
Why are you here?

160
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,600
I have to go to TGL today,

161
00:12:57,160 --> 00:13:01,280
I brought you business management books
to read while I'm gone.

162
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:04,960
Business management?

163
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,639
You didn't listen to a single word I said.

164
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:11,839
- I--
- You need some basic knowledge.

165
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:14,559
That way,
when you attend executive meetings,

166
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,640
you'll understand the discussions.

167
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:20,040
If there's anything
you don't understand, jot it down.

168
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,240
We can talk about it later.

169
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:24,720
Hold on.

170
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:28,160
Don't you feel anything?

171
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,240
About what?

172
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:35,719
You just lost Ms. Claire, your fiancée,

173
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:38,200
but you don't really seem sad.

174
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,840
I think you only need to know
what's necessary.

175
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:03,039
We will make The Paradise project

176
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:05,239
the most expensive development
in the country,

177
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:08,520
but also the most highly sought-after.

178
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:18,880
I love it.

179
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,640
Do you guys love it too?

180
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,999
Then I'm glad.

181
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,599
If everyone agrees,

182
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,240
I'd like us to start working
on this today.

183
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:32,359
Especially the sales and PR departments.

184
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:36,199
I want the plans for this project
on my desk tomorrow morning.

185
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,120
Okay?

186
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:40,959
Hey, why do we have to rush this?

187
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:45,439
Maybe we should start this project
after our 60th anniversary.

188
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:48,399
Because every department
is already so overwhelmed

189
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:50,800
that they can barely keep up.

190
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:54,080
And why do you think
I'm rushing this, Mr. Phichet?

191
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:07,759
It's because I want to
launch this project right

192
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:10,440
at the 60th anniversary of TGL, of course.

193
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:12,559
What about the Agriv project?

194
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:17,360
Weren't we planning to launch
Ms. Claire's Agriv project at this event?

195
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:22,840
Which part of what I said wasn't clear?

196
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,200
Sorry I'm late.

197
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:48,280
I've just been told there would be
a meeting for a new project today.

198
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:53,000
Are you planning to launch your project
on the 60th anniversary?

199
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:59,039
Yes, why?

200
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:00,720
As far as I remember,

201
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:03,760
your project is meant for next year.

202
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,640
If we launch it alongside Agriv,

203
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:09,560
it will create a cash flow shortage.

204
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:14,840
And who told you they would
launch at the same time, huh?

205
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,960
You're launching the project
when the project lead is in that state?

206
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:28,760
You should speak of Ms. Claire in
a better light and show her some respect.

207
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:33,640
Because she holds the most power,
second only to the chairman.

208
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,680
I know that.

209
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:39,360
And I think everyone else knows that too.

210
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:42,960
But are you really
going to be that stubborn?

211
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:47,119
You're launching the project
when the project lead is in that state?

212
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:47,919
It won't survive...

213
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:49,880
I don't think the chairman will be pleased

214
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:53,840
if you replace the project
he and Ms. Claire

215
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:57,360
worked on together with your own project.

216
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,279
Are you using my dad to threaten me?

217
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:04,000
Think whatever you want.

218
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,079
But if you insist on doing this,

219
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:10,200
I will have to report this to him.

220
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:47,920
I thought I made it perfectly clear
why I couldn't approve your project.

221
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:50,600
I didn't come here for that.

222
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:55,759
These are the house designs for Agriv
that Ms. Claire asked me to do.

223
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:59,400
If she's well enough to review them,
please pass them along.

224
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:08,239
I think you know
how much damage the rumors about

225
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:11,440
Ms. Claire and Ms. Cha at your condo
have caused the company?

226
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,320
What does that have to do with the review?

227
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:23,679
Because you don't actually
care about the review.

228
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:26,400
You just wanted to know
how she's doing, right?

229
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,480
Has she fully recovered?

230
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:36,320
Oh, I'm just asking
since her and I used to...

231
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:41,000
work together.

232
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,880
Do you know why you're still working here?

233
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:54,480
Because you're Ms. Cha's boyfriend.

234
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:56,840
As for me,

235
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,960
I'm Ms. Claire's fiancé.

236
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:14,680
Chris.

237
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:16,120
Cha?

238
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:20,720
What are you doing here?

239
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:22,960
It's nothing, Cha.

240
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:25,200
I just brought him some house designs.

241
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,000
Well, Ms. Claire hasn't fully recovered.

242
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:33,880
If you have a question,
you can ask Ms. Cha.

243
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,120
What about you, Ms. Cha?

244
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:44,440
Why did you come to my office?

245
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:51,320
I just came here to tell you
not to humiliate me in a meeting again.

246
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:55,080
Otherwise, I'll get rid of you.

247
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:13,280
Cha. Cha. Cha.

248
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,600
Hear me out, Cha.

249
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:20,839
I admit I went to ask about Claire,
but it was strictly about work, Cha.

250
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:22,919
I didn't mean anything
like what Chan implied.

251
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:25,040
That had better be true.

252
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,440
Cha, listen.

253
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:30,559
Don't you see why Chan's doing this?

254
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:33,239
He doesn't have Claire backing him now.

255
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:35,960
He has to pit us against each other
to survive here.

256
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,440
And what if Claire comes back?
What will you do then?

257
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,479
What can I do?

258
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:44,560
I told you, you're the only one for me.

259
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:46,959
I mean it.

260
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,480
Trust me.

261
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,920
It better be true.

262
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:55,080
You know who got you
to where you are today.

263
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,080
Get the massage room ready for me.

264
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:11,519
Let's go with the chamomile scent today.

265
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,639
So much drama lately.

266
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:13,879
Yes, ma'am.

267
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:16,960
Oh, get the sauna ready for me too.

268
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:20,359
- Could you use the steam room instead?
- What?

269
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:22,680
You know I don't like steam.

270
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,839
Why can't I use it? What's wrong?

271
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:27,799
The temperature control
for the sauna is broken.

272
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:31,200
I've called a technician,
but it won't be fixed until next week.

273
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:35,039
How could it be broken?
It's practically brand new.

274
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:37,479
What if I'd used it
and something happened to me?

275
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:39,120
I'll get it sorted out, ma'am.

276
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:42,320
Then go do it.
Why are you just standing there?

277
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,560
I can't understand any of this.

278
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,000
<i>You can go into any room in this house</i>

279
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:16,040
<i>because everything belongs to you.</i>

280
00:22:57,720 --> 00:22:58,759
Hello?

281
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:00,879
Ms. Claire, what are you doing?!

282
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,760
I was looking for a way to die.

283
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:10,760
You had it so good.
Why would you want to die?

284
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:30,800
Whoa.

285
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:34,160
Why are you standing here? You'll fall.

286
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:37,840
You seem jumpy ever since you got back,

287
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:42,240
I just didn't expect anyone
to be behind me.

288
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:46,120
If you'll excuse me.

289
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:47,920
Hold on.

290
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:57,559
Come on in, it's really relaxing.

291
00:23:57,560 --> 00:23:59,079
Aunt Rin.

292
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:01,320
What did you want to talk about?

293
00:24:02,560 --> 00:24:06,000
Well, our past together, of course.

294
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:11,560
There's actually something
I want to discuss with you.

295
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:15,640
Then let's go talk in the sauna.

296
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:17,280
Let's go.

297
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,960
Ms. Claire, it's me, Tunlathon.

298
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:39,160
Is everything alright?

299
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,520
We're here.

300
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,000
Isn't it a bit too hot?

301
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:08,360
Don't you usually like it hot, Claire?

302
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:14,400
- Right.
- Let's go inside. Come on.

303
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:23,479
Oops, I forgot something.

304
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:24,879
I'll go grab it real quick.

305
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:28,200
Just sit and wait in here.
I'll be right back.

306
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:30,640
Just a second.

307
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:32,200
Okay.

308
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:41,640
Oops.

309
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:43,320
It's everywhere.

310
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:31,960
What are you doing in here?

311
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,600
This is a private area for the family.

312
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,200
It's nothing. I'm sorry.

313
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:49,560
Why isn't she back yet?

314
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:54,320
What are you looking at?

315
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,000
Get out.

316
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:22,000
Help me!

317
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:23,959
Help!

318
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:25,319
Please open the door!

319
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:28,159
Is anyone out there? Open the door!

320
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:29,120
Go on.

321
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:36,120
Please open the door!

322
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:39,600
Please open the door! Aunt Rin!

323
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:41,359
Aunt Rin!

324
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:44,760
Aunt Rin!

325
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,840
Please open the door!

326
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:12,440
No.

327
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:14,640
She's not upstairs either.

328
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:16,359
Split up and look for her.

329
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:17,280
- Sir.
- Sir.

330
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:24,079
Tun, what happened?

331
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,560
How could she disappear?

332
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:27,559
I have no idea.

333
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:29,599
I went to check on her in her room.

334
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:32,239
When she didn't answer, I opened the door.

335
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,200
And she wasn't there.

336
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:36,720
Has the chairman found out yet?

337
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:38,279
No.

338
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:41,199
I told our people to look for her,

339
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:43,960
but to keep things normal
and not let the chairman know.

340
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:49,479
Alright, check the security cameras

341
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:52,399
from when she left her room
until she was last seen.

342
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,759
I'll check her room again.

343
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:54,960
Got it.

344
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:26,880
- This one.
- Yes, sir.

345
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:34,520
- Speed up and see which way she went.
- Yes, sir.

346
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:53,559
Tun, I'm in her room now.

347
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,599
She isn't here.

348
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:56,560
I know where she is.

349
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:18,760
Claire! Claire!

350
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:27,040
Claire?

351
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:28,520
Claire?

352
00:30:29,520 --> 00:30:31,600
Hey.

353
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,920
Hey. Hey!

354
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:41,959
Hey. Hey.

355
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,120
Hey.

356
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:45,720
Hey.

357
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:48,760
Hey, hey.

358
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:51,360
Hey.

359
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,680
You sure she doesn't need a hospital?

360
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:11,840
Her blood pressure's back to normal, sir.

361
00:31:12,360 --> 00:31:15,200
Just keep wiping her down
until her temperature drops.

362
00:31:15,800 --> 00:31:19,519
But don't worry, sir. If anything happens,
I'll take her to the hospital immediately.

363
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,200
But how did this happen?

364
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:32,879
I think you should ask the person
who took her to the sauna, sir.

365
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:33,920
Who?

366
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:36,160
Who locked Claire in the sauna?

367
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:44,200
How is Claire doing?

368
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:46,880
She's safe now.

369
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,920
Luckily, Chan found her in time.

370
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,440
Otherwise,

371
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:56,840
it could have been much worse.

372
00:32:01,600 --> 00:32:02,480
Oh, Claire.

373
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:05,400
Are you okay, Claire?

374
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:08,480
I'm so sorry.

375
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:18,000
I...

376
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:21,400
was the one who invited her to the sauna.

377
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,160
But I left first

378
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:27,639
because I didn't think
there'd be any issues.

379
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:32,119
I know a sauna helps improve
blood circulation to the brain.

380
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,599
So I thought...

381
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:36,400
maybe it would help with her memory.

382
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:39,480
I am so sorry.

383
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,520
It's fine.

384
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,840
You meant well.

385
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:55,480
Let's leave and let her rest.

386
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:58,720
Let me know when she wakes up.

387
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:00,800
I will, sir.

388
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:19,320
Do you think Ms. Rossarin did this
to Ms. Claire on purpose?

389
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:21,000
Yes.

390
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:24,720
We need to keep a closer eye
on Ms. Rossarin.

391
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:28,239
The chairman can't know about any of this.

392
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:31,000
You know his heart isn't doing well.

393
00:33:31,560 --> 00:33:36,920
What we need to do from here on out
is protect her as best as we can.

394
00:33:43,360 --> 00:33:45,680
I'll have the staff prepare some snacks.

395
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:48,720
It'll help Claire regain her energy.

396
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:50,800
Hold on.

397
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,760
You didn't know about the sauna, did you?

398
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:02,320
What are you saying?

399
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:06,040
You think I locked her
in the sauna on purpose?

400
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:09,639
You and Cha barely ever speak to Claire.

401
00:34:11,239 --> 00:34:13,959
Then out of nowhere,
you invited her to the sauna.

402
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:15,920
How could I not suspect anything?

403
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:19,920
Yes.

404
00:34:20,639 --> 00:34:22,120
I did it.

405
00:34:22,639 --> 00:34:24,560
Is that what you wanted to hear?

406
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:28,839
I might have considered it in the past.

407
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:30,120
Do you know why?

408
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,519
Because I was furious.

409
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:34,880
Furious that she lied
I was cheating on you.

410
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:37,479
Furious that you believed
your granddaughter,

411
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:39,440
but didn't believe your own wife.

412
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:44,040
But after she was in the crash
and she lost her memory,

413
00:34:45,199 --> 00:34:46,880
it made me realize something.

414
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:49,800
Life is just too short.

415
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:52,560
I know that...

416
00:34:53,239 --> 00:34:55,280
you probably don't believe anything I say.

417
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:59,640
So believe whatever makes you feel better.

418
00:35:01,960 --> 00:35:02,800
Rin.

419
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:07,640
Yes?

420
00:35:12,040 --> 00:35:15,480
If what you're saying
is actually true, then I'm glad.

421
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:18,800
In that case,

422
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:23,680
from now on, I'll have you
take care of everything in this house.

423
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:28,680
And if anything happens
to Claire inside this house,

424
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:32,040
I will hold you responsible.

425
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:52,360
Sir.

426
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:55,360
Has she woken up?

427
00:35:56,400 --> 00:35:57,719
Not yet.

428
00:35:57,720 --> 00:36:01,600
But I knew you were worried about her,
so I came to check on you.

429
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:05,919
I'm fine.

430
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:07,360
No worries. Thanks.

431
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:14,320
Aside from Claire, you're the only
other person who cares about me.

432
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:18,200
I have another matter
I'd like to discuss with you.

433
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:22,159
I want to ask for your permission

434
00:36:22,160 --> 00:36:25,360
to postpone TGL's
60th anniversary event for now.

435
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:31,600
I mean, it's a massive event, sir.

436
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:34,519
And everyone will be focusing on Claire.

437
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:36,560
If they find out that she...

438
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:38,919
hasn't fully recovered,

439
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:42,639
I'm afraid it will hurt
investor confidence and

440
00:36:42,640 --> 00:36:45,000
hurt our stock price as well.

441
00:36:51,880 --> 00:36:54,240
Will Claire's memory really come back?

442
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:56,599
Maybe not all of it.

443
00:36:56,600 --> 00:37:00,800
But I will try my best to get her back
to normal as much as possible, sir.

444
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:05,720
Hey, Chan.

445
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:12,360
Before Claire's chopper crashed,
did she mention anything to you?

446
00:37:14,120 --> 00:37:15,160
Like what, sir?

447
00:37:17,200 --> 00:37:18,520
I don't really know.

448
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:21,840
But she said she had
something to discuss with me.

449
00:37:22,480 --> 00:37:23,400
But it's okay.

450
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,839
I'm leaving this in your hands.

451
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:31,840
Do whatever it takes to get Claire
as back to normal as possible.

452
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:36,040
Yes, sir.

453
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:41,000
<i>What did you say?</i>

454
00:37:42,040 --> 00:37:44,840
Dad wants to postpone
the 60th anniversary event?

455
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:47,240
<i>I overheard him talking to Chan,</i>

456
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:49,519
so I called to warn you.

457
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:52,199
That way,
you can lobby the other executives

458
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:54,520
to keep everything on schedule.

459
00:37:58,440 --> 00:38:01,200
As if postponing it will
bring Claire back to normal.

460
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:51,600
Why are you scared?

461
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:56,600
Did you forget your own face?

462
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:58,439
<i>I didn't.</i>

463
00:38:58,440 --> 00:38:59,879
<i>I didn't forget.</i>

464
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,719
<i>I didn't do this.</i>

465
00:39:01,720 --> 00:39:02,680
<i>I didn't forget.</i>

466
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,240
No!

467
00:39:16,160 --> 00:39:17,040
How are you feeling?

468
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,680
Hey, what are you doing?

469
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,760
Just checking if your body
has cooled down.

470
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:49,760
It's back to normal.

471
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:00,320
How did I get here?

472
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:03,920
What do you remember?

473
00:40:04,720 --> 00:40:06,040
I...

474
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:10,400
I went to the sauna.

475
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:11,999
And then...

476
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:14,080
I couldn't open the door.

477
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:19,560
Do you know that if you'd stayed
in the sauna just a little longer,

478
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:21,560
you could have died?

479
00:40:24,560 --> 00:40:26,120
Why did you suddenly want a sauna?

480
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:29,480
Who said I wanted one?
It was Aunt Rin's idea.

481
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:33,640
She said she had something
to talk to me about, so she invited me.

482
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:35,720
I see.

483
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:38,800
I looked at the security camera footage.

484
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:41,920
I saw you following her inside,

485
00:40:42,680 --> 00:40:45,400
but when she came back out, she was alone.

486
00:40:47,160 --> 00:40:51,679
Are you saying
Aunt Rin locked me in the sauna?

487
00:40:51,680 --> 00:40:52,560
Exactly.

488
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:55,560
Honestly, it's good this happened,

489
00:40:56,640 --> 00:41:00,400
so you'll finally believe that the people
in this house aren't who they seem.

490
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:05,080
I'll let Mr. Thiwa know you're awake.

491
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,800
Why would Aunt Rin want to hurt me?

492
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:14,000
She doesn't want to hurt you.

493
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,160
She wants to hurt Claire.

494
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:21,960
But what did Claire do?

495
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:25,280
Why does Aunt Rin
want to hurt her so badly?

496
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:33,479
No wonder Aunt Rin is furious.

497
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:36,680
Ms. Claire humiliated her
in front of so many people.

498
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:41,760
But this doesn't justify killing someone.

499
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:46,400
Hey.

500
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:48,520
What if I apologize to her?

501
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:52,360
If I do that,
she might stop holding a grudge.

502
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,000
You can't.

503
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:57,080
Claire never apologized.

504
00:41:58,760 --> 00:41:59,680
So what?

505
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:03,200
You want me to live in constant fear
of being attacked again?

506
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:08,079
I don't know why
Ms. Claire never apologized.

507
00:42:08,080 --> 00:42:10,439
Maybe she was just too proud or something.

508
00:42:10,440 --> 00:42:12,600
But I can do it. I don't mind at all.

509
00:42:15,080 --> 00:42:16,840
But I brought you here to be Claire.

510
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:19,840
Not for her to become you.

511
00:42:40,560 --> 00:42:42,640
Well, Ms. Claire hasn't fully recovered.

512
00:42:44,080 --> 00:42:46,520
If you have a question,
you can ask Ms. Cha.

513
00:42:49,320 --> 00:42:50,920
CLAIRE
CALLING CLAIRE MOBILE

514
00:42:56,920 --> 00:42:59,200
CLAIRE

515
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:03,360
Chris?

516
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:07,480
Cha.

517
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,160
Did you need something?

518
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:12,840
Wanna grab a drink tonight?

519
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:16,080
What's going on, Cha?

520
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:19,320
I just don't want to go home.

521
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:25,360
Can I sleep at your place tonight?

522
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:28,639
Please?

523
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:30,999
Please, please, please.

524
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:32,920
Cha, Cha, Cha, hold on.

525
00:43:33,680 --> 00:43:35,720
Can I take a rain check?

526
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:38,679
What's wrong with you?

527
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:40,800
You never turn me down.

528
00:43:41,560 --> 00:43:42,880
Nothing is wrong.

529
00:43:47,640 --> 00:43:48,840
You miss Claire, don't you?

530
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:57,879
Why would I, Cha?

531
00:43:57,880 --> 00:43:59,640
I don't.

532
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:03,880
If you don't miss her, then prove it.

533
00:44:50,600 --> 00:44:51,600
Claire.

534
00:45:00,160 --> 00:45:01,000
What, Cha?

535
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:04,600
You just said "Claire."

536
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:07,840
You were imagining her just now.

537
00:45:10,040 --> 00:45:11,359
I didn't say that, Cha.

538
00:45:11,360 --> 00:45:12,799
You were hearing things.

539
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:15,159
You're too obsessed with Claire.

540
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:16,520
Hearing things?

541
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:19,840
I heard it loud and clear
that you called me Claire.

542
00:45:21,720 --> 00:45:23,239
- Cha, Cha.
- Let go!

543
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:24,360
Cha!

544
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:30,440
Damn it!

545
00:46:03,400 --> 00:46:04,400
Ms. Claire?

546
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:09,920
Ms. Claire.

547
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:17,440
<i>Mr. Chris?</i>

548
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:23,920
Are you alright?

549
00:46:30,640 --> 00:46:32,079
I was so worried about you.

550
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:33,840
Mr. Chris, what are you doing?

551
00:46:34,840 --> 00:46:36,920
I thought I'd never see you again.

552
00:46:38,400 --> 00:46:39,280
Mr. Chris.

553
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:41,999
Mr. Chris, please let me go.

554
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:44,040
Do you really not remember us?

555
00:46:45,680 --> 00:46:48,240
- No, I don't. I really don't.
- Ms. Claire, I missed you.

556
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:52,440
Please just let me go.

557
00:47:17,120 --> 00:47:18,719
You love being a homewrecker, huh?

558
00:47:18,720 --> 00:47:21,759
<i>What's the deal between
Ms. Claire and Mr. Chris?</i>

559
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:26,159
<i>I heard rumors Ms. Claire and Ms. Cha
had a huge fight over Mr. Chris.</i>

560
00:47:26,160 --> 00:47:28,479
<i>Do you know what I want to do right now?</i>

561
00:47:28,480 --> 00:47:30,079
I want to kill her.

562
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:32,520
But right now,
the one I'm most worried about

563
00:47:33,120 --> 00:47:33,879
is you.

564
00:47:33,880 --> 00:47:36,079
<i>Because once
we gave her Ms. Claire's face,</i>

565
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:38,159
<i>you'd have to see her face every day.</i>

566
00:47:38,160 --> 00:47:40,679
<i>And you'd be the one hurting the most.</i>

567
00:47:40,680 --> 00:47:43,959
I would never get involved with
someone who's already taken.

568
00:47:43,960 --> 00:47:46,120
Can we talk?
